recent_articles.summary:
Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Thursday, Jul. 31.

Apple (AAPL) and Amazon (AMZN) will report quarterly earnings results after the markets close.

Personal Consumption Expenditures (PCE) data for June will be released in the morning. Economists are expecting a slight uptick from May.

Initial jobless claims data for the week ending Jul. 26 will be out in the morning, as economists expect an increase from the previous week.
